# Security Policy

## Supported Versions

We recommend using the latest version of each crate for security updates.

## Reporting a Vulnerability

We take the security of the CSV Protocol seriously. If you believe you have found a security vulnerability, please report it to us as described below.

**Please do NOT report security vulnerabilities through public GitHub issues.**

Instead, please report them via email to [security@csv-protocol.org](mailto:security@csv-protocol.org) with:

- A description of the issue
- Steps to reproduce the issue
- Affected versions
- Any relevant logs, screenshots, or proof-of-concept code

## Response Process

1. Submit your report via email
2. You will receive a confirmation within 48 hours
3. We will investigate and determine our response within 7 days
4. We will release a fix and update the changelog

## Preferred Languages

We prefer all communications to be in English.

## Scope

This security policy applies to all crates in the CSV Protocol workspace and their respective smart contracts.
